This paper discusses meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the model-agnostic meta-learning algorithm (MAML), which is a popular method for meta-learning. The paper also discusses Bayesian hierarchical modeling, which is a statistical modeling technique. Based on these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
